article.headline: Navy 66, Howard 55
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- Chris Harris scored a game-high 22 points and ignited a second-half surge to lead Navy to a 66-55 comeback victory over Howard on Sunday. Navy trailed by six points with 10:13 remaining when Harris hit a deep 3-pointer to begin an 18-5 run. Kaleo Kina scored 11 points and grabbed 7 rebounds for Navy (1-1), which finished the game on a 17-1 run. Jordan Sugars scored 12 points for the Midshipmen, who saw a 32-29 halftime lead evaporate quickly in the second half. Randy Hampton scored 15 points to lead Howard (1-1), which outscored the home team 20-11 to open the second half and take a 49-43 lead with less than 11 minutes to go. But the Bison followed that by going scoreless for a stretch of more than seven minutes.
